GEDEX REALTY CORPORATION, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Joseph T. HIGGINS, Collector of Internal Revenue, Defendant-Appel-lee. No. 35. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 8, 1943. Wickes, Riddell, Bloomer, Jacobi & McGuire, of New York City (Charles W. Tye, of Washington, D. C., of counsel), for appellant. James B. M. McNally, U. S. Atty., and Marvin M. Notkins, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of New York City, for appellee.

Before SWAN, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and FRANK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed on the opinion below, 47 F.Supp. 342.
